{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:32:28.919Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Designing Route Handlers**\n\nI've successfully created a clean setup. Now, I'm shifting focus to designing the route handlers for the Documents API. I'm planning to structure these using a directory with two dedicated files: `route.ts` (for GET and POST) and `[documentId]/route.ts` (for PUT, GET and DELETE). This organization feels logical and scalable.\n\n\n**Analyzing GET Endpoint Logic**\n\nI'm now deeply immersed in the `GET` endpoint logic for `/api/v1/documents/route.ts`. I'm meticulously verifying the supported parameters and query fields, ensuring adherence to the specified requirements. I'm carefully considering the implications of role-based access control, especially regarding admin versus client access and the handling of visibility settings. The auth checks are under review to ensure filters are properly validated.\n\n\n**Refining Access Control**\n\nI'm now integrating the reusable authentication and authorization helper into the project. Specifically, I'm examining the role filtering in `projects/route.ts` to ensure consistency. The current implementation uses client associations and filters projects, and it is a good pattern. I am making sure the logic aligns with the planned approach for documents, especially concerning admin and client permissions.\n\n\n**Clarifying Visibility Logic**\n\nI'm now clarifying document visibility rules within the `/api/v1/documents` `GET` endpoint. I've realized I need to explicitly define what \"where visibility allows\" truly means. Clients, it seems, should be barred from seeing any document marked as `\"admin_only\"`. To enforce this, I'll filter out such documents for non-admin roles. I'm building out the code to enforce this policy.\n\n\n**Expanding Query Filters**\n\nI'm now expanding the query filters for the GET endpoint, to include `project_id`, `document_type`, `status`, `visibility`, and `search`. I'm integrating these filters into the logic, ensuring they function correctly in conjunction with client-based access control. I'm also ensuring the filters handle case-insensitivity, specifically for the project_id to avoid accidental bugs. My next step involves testing these new filters with various combinations of parameters and roles.\n\n\n**Implementing Search Filters**\n\nI'm now implementing the search filter for the GET endpoint. I'm focusing on making the search case-insensitive, and handling null or undefined descriptions gracefully. I am making sure the search query applies to the title, id, and description fields of the document. I am also making sure to trim the query before use.\n\n\n**Defining POST Schema**\n\nI'm now defining the schema for the POST endpoint. It looks like `title`, `document_type`, `client_id` are required, alongside optional fields like `project_id`, `visibility`, `version`, `status`, `owner`, and `desc`. I need to handle default values for those optional fields, and also handle the client-side access control. Non-admin roles will now be denied POST access, as determined by the latest requirements.\n\n\n**Verifying Role Restrictions**\n\nI'm now confirming the restrictions on creating documents, and validating client boundaries on `POST`. I've determined that only \"Admin roles\" are authorized to create documents, and I'm ensuring client roles are correctly prevented from performing the `POST` action, by reviewing the code and applying a valid client_id validation. This involves checking the client_id against a predefined list. I'm ensuring that an invalid client_id returns the correct 400 error.\n\n\n**Validating Required Fields**\n\nI'm now implementing and verifying the necessary checks for required POST fields: `title`, `document_type`, and `client_id`. I'm now checking for the presence, type, and non-emptiness of these fields, returning appropriate 400 errors with descriptive messages if any validations fail. I am now also ensuring that the client_id is validated against a predefined list of valid clients.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:32:28.921Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"o8756ox7","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/api/v1/documents/route.ts","new_text":"import { NextResponse } from \"next/server\";\nimport { \n  API_MOCK_USERS, \n  API_MOCK_DOCUMENTS, \n  verifyJwt, \n  MockUserDbEntry, \n  ApiDocument, \n  getNextDocumentId, \n  getClientNameFromId, \n  getClientIdFromAssociation \n} from \"../../../../lib/api-auth\";\n\nexport const runtime = \"nodejs\";\n\nfunction getAuthCaller(req: Request) {\n  const auth = req.headers.get(\"authorization\");\n  if (!auth?.startsWith(\"Bearer \")) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Missing/malformed Authorization header.\" };\n  }\n  const decoded = verifyJwt(auth.substring(7));\n  if (!decoded?.email) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Invalid/expired access token.\" };\n  }\n  const user = (API_MOCK_USERS as Record<string, MockUserDbEntry>)[decoded.email.toLowerCase().trim()];\n  if (!user) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Authorized user not found.\" };\n  }\n  if (user.status === \"inactive\") {\n    return { status: 403, error: \"Forbidden\", msg: \"This account is inactive.\" };\n  }\n  return { caller: user };\n}\n\nexport async function GET(req: Request) {\n  try {\n    const auth = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (\"status\" in auth) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: auth.error, message: auth.msg }, { status: auth.status });\n    }\n    const { caller } = auth;\n\n    const { searchParams } = new URL(req.url);\n    const clientIdFilter = searchParams.get(\"client_id\");\n    const projectIdFilter = searchParams.get(\"project_id\");\n    const documentTypeFilter = searchParams.get(\"document_type\");\n    const statusFilter = searchParams.get(\"status\");\n    const visibilityFilter = searchParams.get(\"visibility\");\n    const searchQuery = searchParams.get(\"search\");\n\n    let docs = Object.values(API_MOCK_DOCUMENTS) as ApiDocument[];\n\n    // RBAC policy logic\n    if (caller.role !== \"gff_admin\") {\n      const callerClientId = getClientIdFromAssociation(caller.clientAssociation);\n      \n      // Client roles can list/view documents for their client_id where visibility allows (not admin_only)\n      docs = docs.filter(d => d.client_id === callerClientId && d.visibility !== \"admin_only\");\n\n      // Enforce client boundaries if filtering for a different client_id\n      if (clientIdFilter && clientIdFilter !== callerClientId) {\n        return NextResponse.json(\n          { success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Access denied to requested client's documents.\" },\n          { status: 403 }\n        );\n      }\n    } else {\n      // Admin filter by client_id if requested\n      if (clientIdFilter) {\n        docs = docs.filter(d => d.client_id === clientIdFilter);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Apply specific filters\n    if (projectIdFilter) {\n      docs = docs.filter(d => d.project_id.toLowerCase() === projectIdFilter.toLowerCase().trim());\n    }\n    if (documentTypeFilter) {\n      docs = docs.filter(d => d.document_type.toLowerCase() === documentTypeFilter.toLowerCase().trim());\n    }\n    if (statusFilter) {\n      docs = docs.filter(d => d.status.toLowerCase() === statusFilter.toLowerCase().trim());\n    }\n    if (visibilityFilter) {\n      const q = visibilityFilter.toLowerCase().trim();\n      if (caller.role !== \"gff_admin\" && q === \"admin_only\") {\n        return NextResponse.json(\n          { success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Access denied to admin-only visibility.\" },\n          { status: 403 }\n        );\n      }\n      docs = docs.filter(d => d.visibility.toLowerCase() === q);\n    }\n    if (searchQuery) {\n      const q = searchQuery.toLowerCase().trim();\n      docs = docs.filter(d => \n        d.title.toLowerCase().includes(q) || \n        d.id.toLowerCase().includes(q) ||\n        (d.desc && d.desc.toLowerCase().includes(q)) ||\n        d.owner.toLowerCase().includes(q)\n      );\n    }\n\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, documents: docs });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n\nexport async function POST(req: Request) {\n  try {\n    const auth = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (\"status\" in auth) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: auth.error, message: auth.msg }, { status: auth.status });\n    }\n    const { caller } = auth;\n\n    // MVP constraints: admin create/update/delete only\n    if (caller.role !== \"gff_admin\") {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Only administrators can create documents.\" },\n        { status: 403 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    const body = await req.json().catch(() => null);\n    if (!body) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid JSON body.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    const { title, document_type, client_id, project_id, status, version, owner, visibility, desc } = body;\n\n    if (!title || typeof title !== \"string\" || !title.trim()) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Missing or invalid 'title' field.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    if (!document_type || typeof document_type !== \"string\" || !document_type.trim()) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Missing or invalid 'document_type' field.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    if (!client_id || typeof client_id !== \"string\" || !client_id.trim()) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Missing or invalid 'client_id' field.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    const validClients = [\"client-001\", \"client-002\", \"client-003\", \"client-004\"];\n    if (!validClients.includes(client_id)) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid 'client_id' specified.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    const newDocId = getNextDocumentId();\n    const newDoc: ApiDocument = {\n      id: newDocId,\n      title: title.trim(),\n      document_type: document_type.trim(),\n      client_id: client_id,\n      client_name: getClientNameFromId(client_id),\n      project_id: project_id || \"unassigned\",\n      status: status || \"active\",\n      version: version || \"v1.0.0\",\n      owner: owner || caller.name,\n      visibility: visibility || \"internal\",\n      desc: desc || \"\",\n      lastUpdated: new Date().toISOString()\n    };\n\n    (API_MOCK_DOCUMENTS as Record<string, ApiDocument>)[newDocId] = newDoc;\n\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, document: newDoc }, { status: 201 });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n"}}}
