kpoints for multi-agent sandbox execution namespaces.\",\n+    lastUpdated: \"2026-06-27T11:20:00Z\"\n+  },\n+  \"doc-003\": {\n+    id: \"doc-003\",\n+    title: \"Sovereign Route Optimizer Airgap Topology\",\n+    document_type: \"architecture\",\n+    status: \"draft\",\n+    version: \"v0.9.5\",\n+    owner: \"Marcus Vance\",\n+    project_id: \"proj-003\",\n+    client_id: \"client-003\",\n+    client_name: \"Sovereign Logistics Unit [Preview Client]\",\n+    visibility: \"internal\",\n+    desc: \"Network isolation and container topology for route optimization within AWS Nitro Enclaves.\",\n+    lastUpdated: \"2026-06-26T17:45:00Z\"\n+  },\n+  \"doc-004\": {\n+    id: \"doc-004\",\n+    title: \"Federal Enclave Signature Security Policy\",\n+    document_type: \"compliance\",\n+    status: \"active\",\n+    version: \"v1.0.0\",\n+    owner: \"Evelyn Carter\",\n+    project_id: \"proj-004\",\n+    client_id: \"client-004\",\n+    client_name: \"Federal Treasury Division [Preview Client]\",\n+    visibility: \"admin_only\",\n+    desc: \"NIST-compliant security policy governing multi-enclave cryptographic treasury signatures.\",\n+    lastUpdated: \"2026-06-27T08:50:00Z\"\n+  },\n+  \"doc-005\": {\n+    id: \"doc-005\",\n+    title: \"Diagnostics Loop eBPF Event Schema\",\n+    document_type: \"specification\",\n+    status: \"active\",\n+    version: \"v1.1.0\",\n+    owner: \"Auditor Jenkins\",\n+    project_id: \"proj-005\",\n+    client_id: \"client-001\",\n+    client_name: \"Apex Sovereign Group [Preview Client]\",\n+    visibility: \"public\",\n+    desc: \"Detailed eBPF schema defining valid diagnostics telemetry event loops on healthcare nodes.\",\n+    lastUpdated: \"2026-06-27T11:30:00Z\"\n+  }\n+};\n+\n+// Initialize globally to persist edits in memory across hot-reloads\n+if (!(global as any)._apiMockDocuments) {\n+  (global as any)._apiMockDocuments = { ...DEFAULT_API_MOCK_DOCUMENTS };\n+}\n+\n+export const API_MOCK_DOCUMENTS: Record<string, ApiDocument> = (global as any)._apiMockDocuments;\n+\n+export function getNextDocumentId(): string {\n+  const documents = Object.values(API_MOCK_DOCUMENTS);\n+  const ids = documents\n+    .map(d => {\n+      const match = d.id.match(/^doc-(\\d+)$/);\n+      return match ? parseInt(match[1], 10) : 0;\n+    })\n+    .filter(id => id > 0);\n+  const maxId = ids.length > 0 ? Math.max(...ids) : 5;\n+  return `doc-${String(maxId + 1).padStart(3, \"0\")}`;\n+}\n+\n+\n","success":true}],"durationMs":27}}
